<h1>Blog Platform - Rails</h1>

<h2>Run</h2>
<pre>
rails new blog_platform
cd blog_platform
bundle add bcrypt
rails action_text:install
rails generate model User name:string email:string password_digest:string
rails generate model Category name:string
rails generate model Post title:string published:boolean user:references category:references
rails generate model Comment body:text user:references post:references
rails generate controller Sessions new create destroy
rails db:create db:migrate
rails server
</pre>

<h2>Models</h2>
<pre>
class User &lt; ApplicationRecord
  has_secure_password
  has_many :posts, dependent: :destroy
  has_many :comments, dependent: :destroy
end

class Category &lt; ApplicationRecord
  has_many :posts
end

class Post &lt; ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :user
  belongs_to :category
  has_rich_text :content
  has_many :comments, dependent: :destroy
end

class Comment &lt; ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :user
  belongs_to :post
end
</pre>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<pre>
For tags you can either:
1. Add a `tags` string column to posts and store comma-separated tags, or
2. Use the `acts-as-taggable-on` gem for a proper tagging system.
</pre>



# Blog Platform (Rails 8)

This project is a simple blog platform built with Ruby on Rails.
It includes:

- `User` model with `has_secure_password`
- `Category` model
- `Post` model (belongs to user and category, has rich text content)
- `Comment` model (belongs to user and post)
- Basic index pages for `users`, `posts`, `categories`, and `comments`

---

## 1. Prerequisites

Use these versions (or compatible):

- Ruby: `3.2.10` (from `.ruby-version`)
- Rails: `~> 8.1.3`
- SQLite3
- Bundler

Check versions:

```bash
ruby -v
bundle -v
```

